OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772910673
OL,3,CSchool children want kits to treat
OL,4,Cstab wounds to be put in bus stations
OL,6,F That community organisations,
OL,7,Fincluding the Daniel Baird Foundation
OL,8,Fand the Caridon Foundation, have
OL,9,Fdemonstrated the life-saving impact of
OL,10,Fpublicly accessible bleed control
OL,11,Fkits, particularly in areas affected
OL,12,Fby violent crime.
OL,14,F That London's buses and bus stations
OL,15,Fare vital public spaces which
OL,16,Ftransport millions of people daily.
OL,18,F That young Londoners are more likely
OL,19,Fto use the bus and are
OL,20,Fdisproportionately affected by serious
OL,21,Fviolence, particularly knife crime.
OL,26,@nD@AbfvD@AbfzD@Abf
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/5
